I had never heard of TED before, but seems like a great time.  I wish I could be in that room, listening in person, but the podcast version is a resonable substitute.  Some of the guests caught me off guard, but it was a welcome suprise.

All around 10+ on production value and original content. I can and do listen all day every day while I'm at work. No podcast can touch the quickness and efficiency at which they release new episodes. Insane team of sound engineers and story tellers. Please never stop! Long live the snap.
